<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/33c44216fe1c842de27df31db8248f60.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 6 and A = 40 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>7.2</li><li>9.3</li><li>50.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({40}\right)}}}=\frac{{6}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{6}}{{\tan{{\left({40}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{7.1505215555653}\approx{7.2}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={6}^{{2}}+{7.1505215555653}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={36}+{51.129958516603}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={87.129958516603}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{87.129958516603}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{9.3343429611625}\approx{9.3}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{40}^{\circ}\approx{50}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

